[The spreadsheet of data by country, area, or territory for 25 Jun 2021 was not available due to a technical issue and will be included in the next update.

- The Americas region reported 49.3% of daily case numbers and 55.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 71.44 million cases. Brazil reported over 115 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Colombia (29 995), Argentina (27 319), and the USA (14 239); 11 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 13.0% of daily case numbers and 10.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 55.59 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (one case), Switzerland (one case), and Kazakhstan, among others; 6 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 7.8% of daily case numbers and 5.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.82 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (11 734) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Tunisia, Afghanistan, Oman, UAE, Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, and Pakistan. Jordan reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 6.9% of daily case numbers and 4.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.91 million cases. South Africa (16 078) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours, followed by Namibia, Botswana, Uganda, and Zambia. Zimbabwe and Kenya reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Cote d'Ivoire, Rwanda, Gabon, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 4.6% of daily case numbers and 3.0% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.46 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 6000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Mongolia, Japan, Cambodia, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 18.6% of the daily newly reported cases and 20.9% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 34.43 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 51 000 cases, followed by Indonesia (18 872), Bangladesh (5869), Thailand (3644), and Nepal (1721).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 25 Jun 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

