[In the past 24 hours, 10 countries, including Brazil (79 277), India (49 052), Colombia (32 733), Argentina (24 023), Russia (20 393), Indonesia (18 872), South Africa (18 762), the USA (15 537), UK (14 969), and Iran (10 820), have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 8599 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 23 Jun 2021 to late 24 Jun 2021). A total of 46 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 20 of the 46 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 6 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 4 are from the Western Pacific region, and 4 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 4.1%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 12.7%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show an 8.3% decrease in daily reported cases and a 16.3% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily report counted approximately 400 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 181.16 million cumulative reported cases and over 3.92 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
